                     java.net.URI id)
Create an XPath range.

Parameters:
d - the document to which this item is associated.
docuverse - the docuverse the range refers to.
begin - the begin non-negative integer point (if negative, it consider its absolute value) of the range.
end - the end non-negative integer point (if negative, it consider its absolute value) of the range.
context - the xpath expression used to extract the sequence of XML text nodes that will be used as content for calculating the text content of the range.
id - the identifier for the new range.

getTextContent

public java.lang.String getTextContent()

This method retrieves the textual content of the range simply applying the XPath expression specified as context to the docuverse (XML) content and then taking all the value of all the nodes (elements, attributes and text nodes only) returned by the expression, considering the sequence order.

The possible reason of failure in retrieving the text content (i.e., result = "") are:

  • the docuverse does not contain a well-formed XML document
  • the XPath context specified is not a valid XPath expression

Returns:
the textual content retrieved by applying the XPath context onto the docuverse content, or null if some problem happens.
